messages.content:
{
    "thought_on_cooking_style": "The cooking style in the provided examples showcases a mix of techniques including pan-frying, boiling, grilling, and slow cooking. Each recipe emphasizes the importance of seasoning and the use of garnishes to enhance the flavor and presentation of the dish. The recipes also highlight the importance of cooking meat to the desired doneness and allowing it to rest for optimal juiciness.",
    "thought_on_recipe": "For the requested dish of dal chawal with steak, I will combine the traditional Indian dish of dal chawal (lentils and rice) with a pan-fried steak, seasoned appropriately. The dal will be cooked with aromatic spices, while the rice will be steamed to perfection. The steak will be seasoned with a blend of spices that complement the flavors of the dal and will be cooked to the desired doneness. The dish will be garnished with fresh herbs to bring freshness and color.",
    "recipe":
        {
            "title": "Spiced Dal Chawal with Pan-Fried Steak",
            "description": "This dish is a fusion of traditional Indian lentils and rice, known as dal chawal, served with a beautifully seasoned and pan-fried steak. The lentils are simmered with aromatic spices, the rice is steamed until fluffy, and the steak is cooked to perfection with a blend of spices that complement the dal. The dish is garnished with fresh cilantro for an added burst of flavor.",
            "list_of_steps": [
                {
                    "step": "Rinse 1 cup of lentils and soak them in water for 30 minutes, then drain."
                },
                {
                    "step": "In a pot, heat 2 tablespoons of oil and add 1 teaspoon of cumin seeds, letting them sizzle for a few seconds."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Add 1 finely chopped onion to the pot and saut until golden brown."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Stir in 2 minced garlic cloves and 1 teaspoon of grated ginger, cooking for another minute."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Add the drained lentils to the pot along with 1 teaspoon of turmeric, 1 teaspoon of garam masala, 1/2 teaspoon of red chili powder, and salt to taste."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Pour in 4 cups of water, bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until the lentils are tender, about 20-25 minutes."
                },
                {
                    "step": "While the lentils are cooking, rinse 1 cup of basmati rice until the water runs clear, then soak for 20 minutes before draining."
                },
                {
                    "step": "In a separate pot, bring 2 cups of water to a boil, add the drained rice and a pinch of salt, and cook until the rice is tender and the water is absorbed, about 15-18 minutes."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Season the steak on both sides with a mix of 1 teaspoon of ground coriander, 1/2 teaspoon of cumin, 1/4 teaspoon of turmeric, salt, and pepper."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Heat a tablespoon of oil in a pan over medium-high heat and cook the steak for 3-4 minutes on each side for medium-rare, or until desired doneness is reached."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Let the steak rest for 5 minutes, then slice it against the grain."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Fluff the cooked rice with a fork and serve it on a plate alongside the spiced lentils."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Top the dal chawal with slices of the pan-fried steak and garnish with freshly chopped cilantro."
                }
            ]
        }
}
